OL,3,CAdams seeking damages of at least
OL,4,C200,000 euro from BBC, jury hears
OL,6,FGerry Adams is seeking "very
OL,7,Fsubstantial" damages of at least
OL,8,F200,000 euro (#168,000) from the BBC,
OL,9,Fthe jury in his libel action against
OL,10,Fthe broadcaster has heard.
OL,12,FHowever, the British public service
OL,13,Fbroadcaster has argued it would be a
OL,14,F"cruel joke" to award the former Sinn
OL,15,FFein president with any damages.
OL,17,FMr Adams is suing the BBC over what he
OL,18,Fclaims was a "grievous smear" against
OL,19,Fhim, while the organisation described
OL,20,Fthe action as a "cynical attempt to
OL,21,Flaunder his reputation".
