OL,6,FBoth sides in the defamation case have
OL,7,Fconcluded their closing arguments and
OL,8,Fthe jury is in the process of hearing
OL,9,FJudge Alexander Owens' charge.
OL,11,FDeclan Doyle, SC, for Mr Adams, said
OL,12,Fthe damages that should be awarded to
OL,13,Fhis client had to be "very substantial
OL,14,Findeed".
OL,16,FMr Doyle said the "widespread
OL,17,Fcirculation of a national broadcaster
OL,18,Fof an allegation of a cold-blooded
OL,19,Fcynical murder" could not be a
OL,20,Fdefamation of anything other than
OL,21,F"very serious or exceptional".
